===Etymology 1===
{{PIE root|en|leyp}}
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|leven}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|sc=Latinx|lǣfan||to leave}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*laibijaną||to let stay, leave}}, causative of {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*lībaną||to stay, remain}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*leyp-||to stick, fat}}. Cognate with {{cog|ofs|lēva||to leave}}, {{cog|osx|lēvian}}, {{cog|goh|leiban||to leave}}, {{cog|non|leifa||leave over}} (whence Icelandic {{m|is|leifa||to leave food uneaten}}), {{m|is|lifna||to be left}} (whence Danish {{m|da|levne}}). More at [[lave#Etymology_2|lave]], [[belive#Etymology_1|belive]].

